sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a queue with the specified configuration.

Inputs:

  • Folder or Organization Unit - Unique identifier of the folder or organization unit. You can provide value using one of these ways:
    • Use a data pill.
    • Select the value from the Folder or Organization Unit list. In this case, the Folder or Organization Unit ID associated with selected value is used.
  • Name - Custom name for the queue.
  • Description - To add additional information about a queue.
  • Auto Retry - States whether a robot should retry to process an item if after processing, it failed with application exception.
  • Max Number Of Retries - Integer value representing the number of times an item of this queue can be retried if its processing fails with application exception and auto retry is on. Max limit for Retries is 50.
  • Enforce Unique Reference - Reference of the added Queue Item. Reference can be used to link your transactions to other applications used within an automation project.

Outputs:

  • Queue - Details of the queue which got created, populated only when the request is successfully processed. The following field values are fetched:
    • Folder or Organization Unit ID
    • ID
    • Name
    • Description
    • Accept Automatically Retry
    • Max Number Of Retries
    • Enforce Unique Reference
    • Output Data Json Schema
    • Analytics Data Json Schema
    • Creation Time
    • Process Schedule ID
    • SLA In Minutes
    • Risk SLA In Minutes
    • Release ID
    • Folder or Organization Unit Fully Qualified Name
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully. Status is set to "Success". If there is a failure on UiPath, status is set to "Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid folder or organization unit or access denied to it
  • Name already in use
  • Invalid connection URL
  • Invalid credentials
  • Unknown Error. Please check error log for more information


To use this action, a corresponding UiPath Connection and Credential must be created and associated with UiPath Connection & Credential Alias. Learn More

Note :

  • To use the Folder or Organization Unit action input, you must enable either of these UiPath Orchestrator features:
    • Folders Feature to specify Folder
    • Organization Units Feature to specify Organization Unit
  • Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
